CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Turned Down - Student Cordelia Atkins speaks at a meeting to settle the student strike against a history teacher at Rankin High School. Miss Atkins sand she was a cheerleader at a mixed school in Lebanon, Ky., but after her family moved to Rankin, she was overlooked in tryouts for cheerleader at Rankin High School. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of men and women in audience, including Cordelia Atkins standing in center wearing sweater with fringed neck and round floral pendant, gathered in auditorium in McCrady School during school board meeting, Rankin
